{
  "name": "RPlog_And_That_s_No_Small_Thing",
  "title": "And That's No Small Thing",
  "summary": "Aboard the YT-1300 Revenant, the freshly awakened Lynae and the Sith Malus share a long, searching conversation in the cockpit as they fly through the silence and darkness of space. Lynae, newly reconnecting with emotion, marvels at how strange and good it feels to be angry, while Malus draws her out with quotes and gentle philosophy about how feeling defines them and how things said in anger echo with truth. They circle a thorny subject: a woman -- Mitra -- who fears that Lynae will succeed under Malus's auspices, and the question of why she imagines Malus would seek to harm her children. Malus offers to let the teenage Andrev stay aboard the Revenant if speed matters, unbothered by the risk, and the two trade dry wit about loose lips, hubris, and incompetence as the real source of danger. A console chime finally draws Malus back to the controls, and Lynae rises with a wry warning that the next leg of the journey may not be as entertaining as he anticipates.",
